780
00:36:38,640 --> 00:36:41,010
And you better make
sure this kid survives,

781
00:36:41,010 --> 00:36:43,570
because they have an
enormous potential

782
00:36:43,570 --> 00:36:46,470
for having a big reproductive
success later on.

783
00:36:46,470 --> 00:36:47,860
What do you do?

784
00:36:47,860 --> 00:36:52,360
You expend more calories
in taking care of them.

785
00:36:52,360 --> 00:36:55,180
This has been shown in
all sorts of species.

786
00:36:55,180 --> 00:36:59,680
Mate various birds in various
bird species-- mate females

787
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:04,070
with males who are more
attractive versus mating them

788
00:37:04,070 --> 00:37:06,300
with less attractive,
and what you see

789
00:37:06,300 --> 00:37:08,720
is that the females
who have mated

790
00:37:08,720 --> 00:37:14,270
with the more attractive males
give birth to bigger eggs.

791
00:37:14,270 --> 00:37:15,620
That's interesting.

792
00:37:15,620 --> 00:37:18,270
OK, so you're seeing the
evidence of the good genes

793
00:37:18,270 --> 00:37:19,550
coming from the guy.

794
00:37:19,550 --> 00:37:22,610
Male genes have nothing
to do with egg size.

795
00:37:22,610 --> 00:37:25,410
It is how much
protein the mother

796
00:37:25,410 --> 00:37:28,690
puts into the egg production
and the egg development.

797
00:37:28,690 --> 00:37:32,430
And what you see is, she
makes this a self-fulfilling

798
00:37:32,430 --> 00:37:33,400
prophecy.

799
00:37:33,400 --> 00:37:35,510
In a lot of species,
now, it has been

800
00:37:35,510 --> 00:37:39,070
shown that when females mate
with more attractive males

801
00:37:39,070 --> 00:37:42,280
they put more effort into
having the offspring survive.

802
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:43,860
The offspring survive better.

803
00:37:43,860 --> 00:37:45,520
And yes, what do you know?

804
00:37:45,520 --> 00:37:48,010
You really do want to mate
